      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a pretty strong way to frame it for the debaters. it helps them see how to push back against those emotional appeals. to wrap this up, i want to make sure they've got a solid philosophical foundation. if they're asked to defend the moral legitimacy of prioritizing national sovereignty over universal humanitarian concerns, what's the most intellectually sound way to argue that a nation has a moral right—and maybe even a duty—to be selective about who enters?",
